---
import clockTowerImage from '@/assets/clock-tower.jpg';
import clockTowerImageWebp from '@/assets/clock-tower.webp';
---

<section class="section-content">
  <h2 class="section-title">A Gateway to Your American Future</h2>

  <p class="section-text">
    Student EB-5 is your trusted resource for learning about and securing permanent residency through the EB-5 Immigrant Investor Program. We provide high-level analysis on everything EB-5 and are partnered with experienced industry professionals. We have helped educate international students and professionals across the country on the EB-5 process and its opportunities. Our goal has been to provide accurate, relevant, and up-to-date information and analysis so you can make informed decisions with confidence. We are also available for personalized consultations to discuss your goals and options.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-semibold text-foreground mt-12 mb-6">What is the EB-5 Investor Visa Program?</h2>

  <p class="section-text">
    Student EB-5 is a trusted resource for F1 international students, H1B professionals, entrepreneurs, and globally mobile families seeking a pathway to lawful permanent residency in the United States. The EB-5 Immigrant Investor Program was established by Congress in 1990 and the program allows foreign nationals to obtain a green card through a qualifying investment in a U.S. commercial enterprise. Our team provides strategic guidance for individuals navigating immigration challenges, including:
  </p>

  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 section-text space-y-2">
    <li>H1B uncertainty</li>
    <li>visa dependency</li>
    <li>green card backlogs</li>
    <li>OPT exploration concerns</li>
    <li>green card acquisition without employer sponsorship</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="section-text">
    We work closely with clients seeking long-term immigration stability and employer-independent permanent residency solutions tailored to their personal and professional goals.
  </p>

  <p class="section-text">
    Student EB-5 provides personalized support, strategic guidance, and in-depth analysis throughout the EB-5 process. Our team is highly experienced in assisting:
  </p>

  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 section-text space-y-2">
    <li>International students exploring long-term immigration options after graduation</li>
    <li>Tech professionals using EB-5 as a backup immigration strategy amid H-1B uncertainty and Green Card backlogs</li>
    <li>Families seeking long-term residency security and greater immigration stability in the United States</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-semibold text-foreground mt-12 mb-6">Your Path to U.S. Permanent Residency Starts Now</h2>

  <p class="section-text">
    Student EB-5 is a U.S.-based platform connected with experienced EB-5 regional centers, EB-5 attorneys, immigration advisors, and industry professionals to provide international students and foreign professionals with the most comprehensive approach to the EB-5 process. We specialize in helping F1 students, H-1B professionals, STEM graduates, and global families navigate complex immigration challenges including H-1B uncertainty, green card backlog, OPT expiration concerns, and the search for a green card without employer sponsorship.
  </p>

  <p class="section-text">
    Our primary focus is supporting international students and young professionals because this group has been historically underserved in the investment immigration space. We work with students and professionals around the world who are planning to study, work, and build long-term futures in the United States while exploring pathways to permanent residency through investment.
  </p>

  <p class="section-text">
    Understanding EB-5 visa requirements, concurrent filing, rural EB-5 projects, processing timelines, source of funds, and investment options can be overwhelming. We hope to provide detailed <a href="/resources" class="text-primary hover:underline">resources</a>, <a href="/research" class="text-primary hover:underline">insights</a>, and strategic guidance so clients can make informed decisions about their immigration future.
  </p>

  <picture>
    <source srcset={clockTowerImageWebp.src} type="image/webp" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 637px" />
    <source srcset={clockTowerImage.src} type="image/jpeg" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 637px" />
    <img
      src={clockTowerImage.src}
      alt="Historic clock tower representing American heritage and future opportunities"
      class="section-image"
      loading="lazy"
      width={637}
      height={958}
      decoding="async"
      fetchpriority="low"
    />
  </picture>
</section>
